<h2>Common Mistakes</h2>
<p><strong>Mistake 1: Vague prompts.</strong> "Build an SEO tool" produces poor results. Be specific about inputs, outputs, and logic.</p>
<p><strong>Mistake 2: No testing.</strong> Always test with multiple inputs. Edge cases break tools.</p>
<p><strong>Mistake 3: Overcomplicating.</strong> Start simple. Add features later. A working simple tool beats a broken complex tool.</p>
<p><strong>Mistake 4: No landing page.</strong> A tool without context earns fewer links. Explain the problem and demonstrate value.</p>
<p><strong>Mistake 5: Ignoring mobile.</strong> Test on phones. Fifty percent of users are mobile.</p>
